## 7. Monitoring Regulatory Change
[COMPANY] **shall** monitor for changes to applicable laws and regulations through [counsel, regulatory alerts, industry associations]. Identified changes are assessed for impact, the register updated, and any required control changes tracked as corrective actions and reviewed at management review.

## 8. Exceptions
Compliance obligations imposed by law, regulation, or binding contract are **not** waivable through the exceptions process (`../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`). Internal implementation choices may use exceptions, but the underlying legal obligation must still be met.

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The register's completeness and currency are verified at internal audit and management review. Obligation owners are accountable for maintaining satisfying controls and evidence. Noncompliance is escalated to [General Counsel] and leadership; workforce conduct issues are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

